# Design System Rules

- Follow Material Design 3 principles: clear hierarchy, consistent spacing, accessible interactions.
- Use design tokens from `src/styles/tokens.css`; avoid hardcoded colors, spacing, radius, and shadows.
- Shadow scale: `--shadow-sm`, `--shadow-md`, `--shadow-lg`, `--shadow-xl` (derived from `--color-overlay`).
- Overlays/backdrops: `--color-overlay`, `--color-backdrop` (never raw `rgb()` in components).
- Dark mode is default (`data-theme="dark"`); light mode via `[data-theme="light"]`.
- Theme toggle and language switch live in `SiteToolbar` (fixed, top inline-end).

## Typography

- Variants only: `headline`, `body1`, `body2`, `button`, `caption` via `Typography.astro`.
- **English:** Raleway (`html[lang="en"]`).
- **Farsi:** Vazirmatn (`html[lang="fa"]`).

## Shared CSS

- Global entry: `src/styles/global.css` imports `tokens.css`, `utilities.css`, `links.css`, `components.css`.
- Put cross-component UI (toolbar, social links, modals) in `components.css`, not duplicated in scoped component styles.
- Component-specific layout/animation may stay in `ComponentName.styles.astro` with `is:global` when it must affect slotted or child markup.

## Interactive UI

- Ensure `focus-visible` styles on buttons and links.
- Modals use native `<dialog>` + `showModal()`; center with flex on the dialog, panel inside `.popup-modal__panel`.
- Prefer composition with layout primitives before custom wrappers.
